r as an in-tool preprocessing helper); `apps/tooling/tools/game_detector.py` (Tool 1 — black-screen detection; replaced by `in_match_detection` zones); `apps/tooling/tools/black_screen_detector.py` (same era); `apps/tooling/tools/bsd_roi_debugger.py` (debugger for the above; obsolete); `apps/tooling/tools/frame_labeler.py` (Tool 2 — Tool 6 `video_timeline_labeler.py` supersedes); `apps/tooling/tools/warden_analyzer.py` (Tool 5 — Story 9-2 cancelled; HUD 2.0 footage breaks its legacy ROIs); `apps/tooling/tools/points_state_detector.py` (legacy dead code). Plus: `apps/tooling/wardentooling.py` registrations stripped (flow-functions + `_TOOL_MAP` entries + `choices_main` branches + `menu_main` branches + `_reprompt_source` branches for each retired module). Plus: `apps/tooling/tests/test_*.py` files for retired tools deleted (verify each before delete). Plus: `apps/tooling/config/config.yaml` legacy `minimap_identification:87-907` block — decision at create-story (recommendation: delete it since unreferenced once 9-9c emitter doesn't read from config.yaml). Sequencing: ideally lands after 9-9c (so `map_config_emitter.py` no longer transitively imports retired helpers) OR before 9-12/9-13/9-14 (so new tools don't accidentally import about-to-die modules). Sprint fit: fits-in-one-sprint (~1 day mechanical). Track C. Pre-production posture (no backward-compat) makes this safe. See _bmad-output/sprint-change-proposal-2026-05-15.md.
   9-12-unified-zone-picker: backlog  # NEW 2026-05-15 (Stephane, /bmad-correct-course). New tool: `apps/tooling/tools/zone_picker.py` (single-file OR single-package — decide at create-story based on size). Interactive Tk picker collapsing workflow steps #2/#3/#4 into one tool with 3 selectable modes: (1) HUD-version mode — input = cross-version PNGs (any class from each `labeled/v<hud>/`); output target = `hud_version_detection: Zone[]` in the v<hud> fragment; (2) In-match mode — input = positive class pooled from any `labeled/v<hud>/<MAP_LABELS_slug>/`, negative class pooled from `labeled/v<hud>/{lobby,score,transition}/`; output target = `in_match_detection: Zone[]`; (3) Per-map mode — input = `labeled/v<hud>/<map_slug>/`; output target = `minimap_identification.maps.<map_slug>.zones: Zone[]` with `weight` + `weight_override` editing for 100%-accurate per-map ID. Reuses `apps/tooling/tools/image_inspector/` primitives (ImageCanvas + HSVEditor — no GUI reinvention). Reuses `apps/tooling/tools/common/video_player.py` if frame-stepping is required. Folds in `overlay_stack_analyzer`'s variance/heatmap signal as an in-tool preprocessing helper (compute mean + stddev + Hue-stability heatmap on the fly per labeled class — no separate Tool 7 needed). Writes zone fragments to `apps/tooling/output/zones/v<hud_version>/{hud_version_detection,in_match_detection,minimap_identification}.json` (final layout at create-story) that `map_config_emitter.py` consumes. Pytest for pure logic (fragment serialization + variance helper); no Tk GUI testing per Tool 6/8 precedent. `wardentooling.py` registers zone_picker as a top-level menu entry. Dependencies: 9-9c (target schema shape); 9-11 (retires the predecessors this tool replaces — sequencing 9-9c → 9-11 → 9-12 safest). Sprint fit: fits-in-one-sprint, possibly two (GUI complexity: Tk modes, HSV sliders, variance preprocessing, per-map weight controls — likely 3-5 days focused work; estimate at create-story). Track C. See _bmad-output/sprint-change-proposal-2026-05-15.md.
   9-13-video-detection-tester: backlog  # NEW 2026-05-15 (Stephane, /bmad-correct-course). New tool: `apps/tooling/tools/video_test.py` (single-file shape like Tool 7/9 precedent — pure helpers + thin `main(argv) -> int`). Headless tool that consumes an emitted `map_config.<hud_version>.json` and runs the full detection pipeline against an actual video. CLI: `python tools/video_test.py <video.mp4> [--config <map_config.json>] [--output <results.json>]`. Pipeline stages: (a) i-frame extraction via `cv2.VideoCapture` + configurable stride (default ~1 i-frame/sec); (b) once-per-session HUD-version classification via `hud_version_detection` zones → selects which `map_config.<hud>.json` applies (if multiple bundled); held constant for the run; (c) per-i-frame binary `in_match` classification via `in_match_detection` zones (argmax_above_threshold over zone-fire ratio, same mechanism as Tool 9); (d) state machine — on rising edge → enter `in_match`; on falling edge → enter `score_screen` for `score_screen_duration_ms` (frames in this window flagged for score-screen extraction); after the score window → `not_in_match` (lobby/transition merged; not differentiated) until next rising edge; (e) for frames inside an `in_match` span → map-ID classification via `minimap_identification` (weighted); hold the most-confident map-ID across the span as canonical. Output `results.json` shape: top-level `hud_version` + ordered list of `{frame_idx, timestamp_ms, state ∈ {in_match, score_screen, not_in_match}}` + `matches: [{start_frame, end_frame, map_id, confidence}, ...]`. Reuses Tool 9's per-frame zone-fire logic (no reinvention). Pytest for pure logic (pipeline stage helpers, state machine, i-frame stride math) + manual smoke test against ≥1 real EVA capture. `wardentooling.py` registers video_test. Dependencies: 9-9c (target schema + score_screen_duration_ms field); ideally 9-12 (populated zone configs to test against) + 9-14 (HUD-version classifier already exercised on labeled PNGs). Sprint fit: fits-in-one-sprint (~2-3 days). Track C. Closes workflow step #6 (end-to-end video pipeline). See _bmad-output/sprint-change-proposal-2026-05-15.md.
   9-14-roi-detection-tester-refit-for-unified-schema: backlog  # NEW 2026-05-15 (Stephane, /bmad-correct-course). Refit `apps/tooling/tools/roi_detection_tester.py` (Tool 9) for the unified schema. Three classifiers: (a) HUD-version (NEW) — ground truth = `v<hud_version>/` parent directory of each labeled frame; predicted = running `hud_version_detection` zones; (b) binary `in_match` / `not_in_match` (REPLACES existing 4-way `{lobby, in_match, score, transition}` cascade classifier) — ground truth = `true` if frame's folder is in MAP_LABELS, `false` otherwise (`lobby`/`score`/`transition` folders); predicted = `in_match_detection` zones argmax_above_threshold; (c) per-map ID (UNCHANGED). Tool 6 labeler stays UNCHANGED — still produces 4-folder structure (lobby/score/transition/<map>); the binary collapse happens in Tool 9's ground-truth derivation. `report.json` schema rewritten with three classifier sections (`hud_version_classifier`, `in_match_classifier`, `map_id_classifier`) — old 4-way `game_state_classifier` section removed (or renamed to `in_match_classifier` with binary confusion). `summary.md` rewritten in canonical order: HUD-version → in_match → map-ID. `frame_predictions.csv` opt-in columns: `frame_path, ground_truth_hud_version, predicted_hud_version, ground_truth_in_match, predicted_in_match, ground_truth_map_id, predicted_map_id` + per-classifier confidence. Pytest refit: existing 4-way game-state tests deleted/rewritten as binary; new HUD-version tests added; per-map tests preserved. Empty-zones backward-compat preserved (if `hud_version_detection` or `in_match_detection` is empty → classifier short-circuits to `unknown` for every frame + summary reports `accuracy 0.000 — zones unpopulated`, mirrors Tool 9 precedent). Dependencies: 9-9c (new schema). Sprint fit: fits-in-one-sprint (~1-2 days). Track C. See _bmad-output/sprint-change-proposal-2026-05-15.md.
